                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/362: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-15T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 15, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 15—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Rumanian Legation informs me that it granted transit visa without stopover on
                    consular registration and identity certificate to Insull this morning and that
                    it expects him to arrive at Constanza on Polish flag vessel <hi rend="italic"
                        >Polonia</hi> leaving Piraeus tomorrow, March 16th. Rumanian Legation
                    understands that fugitive’s destination is Poland via Tcheko-slovakia.
                        Owsley<note n="33" xml:id="d478fn33">Alvin M. Owsley, Minister in
                        Rumania.</note> here asks you inform Holmes<note n="34" xml:id="d478fn34"
                        >Julius Cecil Holmes, Third Secretary of Legation in Rumania.</note> unless
                    already done.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
